Am I the only one who needs to watch a show before falling asleep?😂 It’s my time to relax when the day is over. I know there’s a million things that are better to do instead, but it’s just so hard to give this up😂

A year full of memories and incredible life changes🙌🏼🎉 From buying our first home, traveling to 8 different countries, officially starting my podcast, doubling both our incomes, making tons of new friends, and strengthening our marriage to a whole new level❤️ I know this video is just a highlight “reel”, so to be clear our life hasn’t been perfect. We’ve had many hardships this year that came unexpectedly, including loss, illness, uncertainty, grief, and glimpses of depression. Life is a grand mixture of the entire spectrum of human emotions - with joy comes it’s opposite, which in turn makes it so sweet. If I’ve learned anything in life so far, it’s to ride with the waves; you’ll never learn to surf in calm waters. 🌊

I’m truly so grateful for all that I have learned this year, and for all of our blessings. I’m grateful for the opportunity to live such a full life, and to do so with my best friend❤️ This year was truly AMAZING 🤩🥹 It honestly feels like 2 years squeezed into 1. I’m honestly just so grateful🫶🏼 Now that I’ve honored 2022 and all that it brought, cheers to the New Year!!🥂✨ 2023 is going to be so special🙌🏼

I recently tried out a resource and want to share it with you guys, because it’s very different! For those who are healing and looking for something other than talk therapy, google Orit Krug - it uses the remarkable process of Dance Therapy and nervous system techniques to help heal deep rooted issues that so many of us deal with. It’s beautiful to see how this type of therapy can help us connect with our bodies and help heal from things like unhealthy cycles, childhood trauma, negative core-beliefs, marriage problems, communication blocks, emotional triggers, body image, confidence, etc. If you’ve tried talk therapy and feel like you need something different to help you achieve your goals, you can give this a try! My personal experience was helpful and really special. They have an 8-month program called “Let Love In : Heal Trauma” that seems like a more in-depth experience. They also have a program for couples! You can hear more testimonials through the link in my bio!🫶🏼
Good thing they have a great return policy for all the women out there doing “retail therapy”😂🛒

I hope everyone had a very happy Easter 🤍✨ 
This was my favorite Easter so far. The last few days have been the greatest blessing ever🙏🏼 I’m so grateful for my Savior, Jesus Christ. He is my redeemer and my best friend. He died for each of us - to think that he suffered every pain I have experienced, am currently experiencing, and will ever experience… It is a form of divine love where gratitude cannot possibly be found in words. I owe everything to my Heavenly Father and my Savior. I’m grateful that I was able to spend time this weekend, thinking about the time in the Savior’s life where He suffered, died, and lived again. 

I really loved something my aunt shared this weekend when reciting the words of the hymn “I’m A Child of God”. She shared the lyrics “…teach me, guide me, walk beside me, help me find the way. *Teach me all that I must do*…” My aunt shared how special it is to think if we replaced the word “do” with “be” - because ‘doing’ one thing is different than it becoming the essence of our being. 

I’m far from perfect - I’ve been struggling with a faith crisis for the past year or so, one reason being similar to the concept of “why does God let bad things happen to good people”. And although I don’t have all the answers, I do know this. God is real, and my Savior died for me. He understands me more than anyone ever could. I know that regardless of any pain points or confusion I experience, I can always rely on my Heavenly Father and my Savior, because above all else, they are what matters most. 

I’ve missed making my Savior the priority in my daily life and I’ve had incredible experiences as I’ve made an intentional effort to do it again like I did before. If you’re at all struggling with spirituality or religion, I just want you to know that you’re never alone and Jesus Christ knows you, understands you, and loves YOU❤️

Happy Easter🐣🫶🏼
